Notes

1. When the next page (fol. 105v) begins, the text is discussing Libra. This seems to be a textual lacuna, as there is no sign of physical loss from any of the (admittedly late) foliations and Libra immediately follows Virgo, so it is not clear what an entire missing folio, if that be the cause, would have contained in order to span the gap.

2. A suspension stroke was inscribed above the tironian et that concludes "soiget" but it appears to have been partially scrubbed out; it is not clear what it was meant to stand for.

3. Abyssinia?

4. Burgundy?

5. Why the constellations being "buried" should explain them being called "changeable", and what this means anyway, is not clear. Perhaps this verb is instead a form of con-imchloí ("changes").
